OL,3,GOPINIONCThe return of the ITV News at
OL,4,CWhen
OL,5,
OL,6,FIt looks like News at When is back on
OL,7,FITV 1.
OL,9,FEvery night for the next fortnight,
OL,10,FNews at Ten will be significantly late.
OL,12,FSome nights it will be shown at
OL,13,F10.15pm, delayed by I'm a Celebrity
OL,14,FSouth Africa.
OL,16,FOn other occasions it will be as late
OL,17,Fas 10.30pm because of other programmes
OL,18,Fincluding The Assembly.
OL,23,EPub: 03-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,145,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14402
SC,0002
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F144A1776459559
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/5
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCThe return of the ITV News at
OL,4,CWhen
OL,5,
OL,6,FOf course, ITV 1 regularly bounces News
OL,7,Fat Ten back. But this looks like a
OL,8,Fstrategy ` not specific decisions
OL,9,Fconcerning individual programmes.
OL,11,FCommercial broadcasters can hardly be
OL,12,Fblamed for wanting to maximise ratings
OL,13,Fand revenue.
OL,15,FThanks to the hour-long Evening News at
OL,16,F6.30pm, there is no suggestion of ITV
OL,17,Ffailing to meet Ofcom commitments.
OL,19,FBut I really do think ITV needs to
OL,20,Fcommit to a fixed slot for its late
OL,21,Fevening news.
OL,23,EPub: 03-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,145,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14403
SC,0003
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F144A1776459559
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/5
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCThe return of the ITV News at
OL,4,CWhen
OL,5,
OL,6,FI would rather see the programme firmly
OL,7,Fanchored at 10.30pn than cast around.
OL,9,FI never quite got the rationale for the
OL,10,Fdecision to bring back News at Ten in
OL,11,F2008. It seemed to have more to do with
OL,12,Fa belated concern for the damage done
OL,13,Fwhen the programme was axed in 1999.
OL,15,FOr did moving the news simply mean 30
OL,16,Fminutes less had to be commissioned for
OL,17,Fthe evening schedule?
OL,19,FBy fixing the programme at 10.30pm,
OL,20,Fviewers would be able to enjoy some
OL,21,Fcertainty.
OL,23,EPub: 03-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,145,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14404
SC,0004
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F144A1776459559
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/5
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCThe return of the ITV News at
OL,4,CWhen
OL,5,
OL,6,FMeanwhile those of us who follow the
OL,7,Fnews closely would be able to watch
OL,8,Fboth the BBC News at Ten and ITV's late
OL,9,Fevening bulletin. I've never been
OL,10,Fcomfortable with the two programmes
OL,11,Fcompeting head-to-head.
OL,13,FBy the same token, the BBC's occasional
OL,14,Ftendency to delay the News at Ten needs
OL,15,Fto be nipped in the bud.
OL,17,FMeanwhile it's still unclear whether
OL,18,Fthe ITV Lunchtime News has moved
OL,19,Fpermanently to 12.30pm. Or is this
OL,20,Fsimply an arrangement while Loose Women
OL,21,Fis off?
OL,23,EPub: 03-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
